Hardware:
Basic Hardware:
CPU: Intel i5/Ryzen 5 (min), Intel i7/Ryzen 7 (recommended)
RAM: 8 GB (min), 16 GB (recommended)
Storage: 500 GB SSD (min), 1 TB SSD (recommended)
GPU: Integrated graphics (min), NVIDIA GTX 1660 (recommended for AI models)
Network: High-speed internet connection

Advanced Hardware:
CPU: Multi-core processors (Intel Xeon/AMD EPYC)
RAM: 32 GB or more
Storage: 2 TB SSD or cloud storage
GPU: NVIDIA RTX 3080 or equivalent
Cooling/Power: Adequate cooling and UPS for server setups


Software:

1. Operating System:

Windows 10/11 or Linux (Ubuntu/Debian)

2. Programming Languages:

Python (primary), R (optional)

3. Libraries/Frameworks

TensorFlow / PyTorch (deep learning)

Scikit-learn (ML algorithms)

Pandas, NumPy (data processing)

Matplotlib, Seaborn (visualization)

NLTK, spaCy (NLP)

4. APIs/Data Fetching:

Alpha Vantage, Yahoo Finance (financial data)

5. Database:

MySQL, PostgreSQL, or MongoDB

6. Cloud/Virtualization:

Docker, AWS, Google Cloud (optional)

7. Development Tools:

Jupyter Notebook, VS Code, or PyCharm
